{"id":1257,"date":"2020-02-26T13:10:58","date_gmt":"2020-02-26T13:10:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/drqadar.vibrantdynamics.com\/?page_id=1257"},"modified":"2023-06-05T02:57:38","modified_gmt":"2023-06-05T02:57:38","slug":"board-members","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/rehmatqadir.org\/board-members\/","title":{"rendered":"Board Members"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<div class=\"brz-root__container brz-reset-all\">\n<section id=\"cpstwuynderkwweidkizzsobzkvzhzliberx\" class=\"brz-section brz-css-sbcej\" data-uid=\"cpstwuynderkwweidkizzsobzkvzhzliberx\">\n<div class=\"brz-section__items\">\n<div class=\"brz-section__content\" data-custom-id=\"iupelgjaxcbxefgwxahwycorhyfkwyonmcvu\">\n<div class=\"brz-bg brz-css-ihgwe brz-css-miwwv\">\n<div class=\"brz-bg-content\">\n<div class=\"brz-container__wrap brz-css-crqqp\">\n<div class=\"brz-container brz-css-excey\">\n<div class=\"brz-wrapper brz-css-vrazu\">\n<div class=\"brz-d-xs-flex brz-css-exzda\">\n<div class=\"brz-rich-text\" data-custom-id=\"rwrphfsnkmchnaxqlpernqoqgawgojrwyuhe\">\n<h2>Board Members in the United States:<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ghulam Qadir, M.D.<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Qadir is the President and Treasurer of the Rehmat Foundation. He is a Board-Certified Psychiatrist with a sub-specialty in Addiction and Geriatric Psychiatry and a certified psychiatric administrator. Dr. Qadir is a fellow of the Academy of Consultation\/Liaison Psychiatry and a distinguished life fellow of the American Psychiatric Association. He has been in practice in Dearborn, Michigan since 1978. In addition, he served as chief of Psychiatry at Oakwood Healthcare for 14 years. Currently, he serves as CEO of Apex Behavioral Health Dearborn. Dr. Qadir attended Nishtar Medical College in Multan Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Huda Zenati, Ph.D., LMSW, MS, ACSW<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Zenati is the secretary of the Rehmat Foundation. She has practiced psychotherapy since 1994 and currently works at Apex Behavioral Health in Dearborn, Michigan. In addition, she was previously a reporter, and an editor, and taught Journalism at Yarmouk University in Jordan. Dr. Zenati has been a speaker at multiple international conferences about mental health issues.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Ahmad Saeed Khan, M.D.<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Khan is a Philanthropist and a member of the Board. He is a Board-Certified pediatrician and practices in Kingman, Arizona. Dr. Khan attended Nishtar Medical College.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Mohammed J. Iqbal, M.D.<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Iqbal is a Philanthropist and a member of the Board. He is a Board- Certified urologist and practices in Elizabethtown, Kentucky. Dr. Iqbal attended \u00a0Nishtar Medical College.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>M. Aslam Barra, M.D.<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Barra is a member of the Board. He is a board-certified obstetrician\/gynecologist and practices in Hollister, California. Dr. Barra attended Nishtar Medical College.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Muhammad Aslam<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Aslam is a member of the Board and a businessman in Westland, Michigan. Mr. Aslam is from the Multan area in Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Arif Seyal MD<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Clinical Professor of Medicine, University of California, Davis, Sacramento, California.<\/li>\n<li>Division of Allergy and immunology Special interest in severe asthma, primary immunodeficiency, air pollution, urticaria Angioedema, food, and drug-allergy Philanthropist.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Saba Syed MD, FACLP, DFAPA<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Syed is a member of the Board. She is Health Sciences Clinical Professor of Psychiatry at The David Geffen School of Medicine, University of California, Los Angeles. She is Chief of the Consultation &amp; Liaison Psychiatry and Chair of Bioethics, Olive View- UCLA Medical Center.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Ghulam Rasul Chauhdry, PhD<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Chauhdry is a member of the board. He is a Professor of Molecular Biology at Oakland University, Rochester, Michigan. He is the Director of OU-WB Institute for Stem Cell and Regenerative Medicine.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Ayesha Khan MD, FACOG<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Khan is a member of the board. She is the Associate Director of OB\/GYN Residency Program, at Corewell Health Dearborn, Michigan. She is an Associate Professor of Obstetrics and Gynecology, at Wayne State University, School of Medicine, Detroit, Michigan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>Board Members of Rehmat Foundation in Multan, Pakistan:<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Khawaja Muhammad Younus<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Khawaja Younus is the chairman of the board.<\/li>\n<li>He is a philanthropist and leading businessman and lives in Multan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Khalil Ahmad<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Ahmad is the vice-chairman of the board. He is a retired senior civil servant and lives in Multan, Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Mr. Ayub Shah<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Shah is a Philanthropist and the Secretary of the Board. He is the managing director of Mahmood Textile Mills and lives in Muzaffar Garh.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Mr. Hyder Jamal<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Jamal is the Finance Secretary of the Board. He is an attorney and advocates for the supreme court of Pakistan. He is from Multan, Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Wasima Tallat, MBBS, DGO, MCPS<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Tallat is the joint secretary of the board. She retired as a Lieutenant colonel from Pakistan Army Medical Corps. She served as head of obstetrics\/gynecology for 10 years at CMH Multan. She is a leader in her specialty in Multan. She is a philanthropist who brings a wealth of clinical, and administrative experience.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Naweed Ahmad Sadiq<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Sadiq is the Information Secretary of the Board. He is an ophthalmologist and practices in Multan, Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Mr. Muhammad Irfan<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Irfan is the coordination secretary of the board. He is an attorney and Finance Secretary of the Multan District Bar.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><strong>Advisors:<\/strong><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dr. Rana Altaf Ahmad (Chief Advisor)<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Professor of Anesthesiology, Vice-Chancellor, Nishtar Medical University, Multan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Fayyaz Hussain, Ph.D.<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Hussain is a Professor in the Center for Integrative Studies at Michigan State University.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Syed Muhammad Ali Bukhari, MD, MRCSEd(U.K), FCPS (PAK)<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Bukhari is a fellow of Pediatric Cardiac Surgery, at George Washington\u00a0 University, and Children&#8217;s National Medical Centre, Washington DC USA. Assistant Professor of Pediatric Cardiac Surgery at\u00a0 Children&#8217;s Hospital in Multan, Pakistan.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Atiq Warraich<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Warraich is serving as Web Program Director in the U.S. Department of Energy. He manages all aspects of the Department\u2019s primary public-facing website, <a title=\"Read more about Energy.gov\" href=\"https:\/\/www.energy.gov\/\" aria-label=\"Read more about Energy.gov\">Energy.gov<\/a> &#8211; including the web development team, CMS support team, cyber security, and cloud hosting. He has been part of the Digital Reform Project, an effort to cut wasteful spending and improve user experience by consolidating the agency&#8217;s public-facing websites onto a single, mobile-first, open-source platform.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr.\u00a0<span class=\"il\">Mubashir<\/span>\u00a0Mushtaq Daha<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Daha is a Registrar in the Department of Dermatology and Deputy Director of Special Initiatives at PIMS in Islamabad. He is a Nishtarian and has Masters of Science in Public Health from Quaid-e-Azam University, Islamabad. He is the General Secretary of PMA Islamabad. He is also CEO of Taaleem Foundation, Heath Initiative. He was Deputy Director of International Coordination in the Prime Minister\u2019s Office from 2011-2020.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Zafar Iqbal Qadir PhD<\/strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Dr. Qadir is a retired federal secretary of IT and telecommunications. He has extensive administrative, legal, trade, IT, and diplomacy experience at national and international level. Dr. Qadir is the founder and chairman of Taaleem Foundation which operates a chain of high-performing grammar schools in underprivileged areas of Baluchistan. He is the owner of ITC4E consulting which provides innovative solutions to education technologies. The e-School is a platform of virtual schools operated by ITC4E. He is also the director of \u201cIqbal Institute for Policy Studies \u201c a think tank. Dr. Qadir is chairman of the board of \u201cinnoversity\u201d an online training program in Pakistan. He is on the visiting faculty at the University of Cambridge in the Uk. Dr. Qadir will be our lead in education.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text] Board Members in the United States: Ghulam Qadir, M.D. Dr. Qadir is the President and Treasurer of the Rehmat Foundation. He is a Board-Certified Psychiatrist with a sub-specialty in Addiction and Geriatric Psychiatry and a certified psychiatric administrator. Dr. Qadir is a fellow of the Academy of Consultation\/Liaison Psychiatry and a distinguished life fellow &hellip; <\/p>\n<p class=\"link-more\"><a href=\"https:\/\/rehmatqadir.org\/board-members\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading<span class=\"screen-reader-text\"> &#82